line_1: My Life, my Blood I here present;
line_2: If for thy Truth they may be spent,
The Place was apt, the Pastime pleasant;

line_1: Nor yet those awful joys present,
line_2: For chiefs and heroes only meant:

line_1: That their cleft piles on Tyber's plains present,
line_2: His golden sceptre broke, and purple mantle rent.

line_1: Then, wou'd the Piece fresh Beauties still present,
line_2: Nor Length of Time wou'd leave the Eye content:

line_1: Their gifts, with prostrate homage, they present;
line_2: His gracious smiles their rising doubts prevent;

line_1: But thou, should tempting villainy present,
line_2: All Marlb'rough hoarded, or all Villiers spent,

line_1: When dreary visions shall at last present
line_2: Thy vengeful image in the midnight tent,
Then he in haste this letter sent,

line_1: The Painters thus by Contraries present
line_2: The allegorick Devil like the Saint,
Tippet too from Tail of Pheasant!

line_1: And there to Ely doth her Son present:
line_2: Led by Elkanah, unto Shilo went,
